#originalTopic=Gun_Ownership_Should_Be_Strictly_Controlled
 YES.  But controlled doesn't have to mean there are no guns out there.  It could mean a) really good background checks, b) a waiting period, c) mandatory training in safety and even in target practice, and d) mandatory gun lock rules so kids and criminals are less likely to get there hands on it.